---
import ServiceLayout from '../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import ProcessSteps from '../components/ProcessSteps.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const title = "Engine Bay Cleaning Fort Lauderdale | Mobile Service | Route95";
const description = "Professional engine bay cleaning in Fort Lauderdale. Mobile service - we come to you! Degrease and detail your engine compartment. Call 754-215-2272";

const parentCategory = {
  href: `${base}car-detailing-services-fort-lauderdale/`,
  title: "Car Detailing Services"
};
---

<ServiceLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  h1="Engine Bay Cleaning Fort Lauderdale"
  intro="Engine bay cleaning removes grease, grime, and dirt from under your hood, making maintenance easier and keeping your engine running cooler."
  currentPage="/engine-bay-cleaning-fort-lauderdale/"
  parentCategory={parentCategory}
>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
    <div class="lg:col-span-2 space-y-8">
      <section>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          A clean engine bay isn't just about appearance. When oil, grease, and dirt coat your engine and its components, heat doesn't dissipate as efficiently. Fluid leaks become impossible to spot. And every mechanic who looks under your hood forms an impression of how well the car has been maintained.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          We bring engine bay cleaning directly to your Fort Lauderdale location. Using professional-grade degreaser and careful technique, we restore your engine compartment to like-new condition without risking water damage to sensitive electronics.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          Engine bay cleaning is especially valuable when selling a vehicle. Buyers judge maintenance history partly by how clean the engine looks.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-4">How Much Does Engine Bay Cleaning Cost in Fort Lauderdale?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong>Engine bay cleaning in Fort Lauderdale costs $75 to $150 depending on engine size and how dirty it is.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          A well-maintained engine that just needs a refresh falls on the lower end. Heavily neglected engine bays with caked-on grease and road grime require more degreaser and time. We assess the situation and give you an exact quote.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-4">How Long Does Engine Bay Cleaning Take?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong>Engine bay cleaning takes 30 to 60 minutes depending on condition and level of detail required.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          We let the degreaser work before agitatingâ€”rushing this step means less effective cleaning. After rinsing, we dry all components and apply protectant to plastic and rubber parts.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-4">Why Clean Your Engine Bay?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong>A clean engine runs cooler, shows problems earlier, and impresses mechanics and potential buyers alike.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Benefits of engine bay cleaning:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-4 space-y-2">
          <li>Better heat dissipation from clean surfaces</li>
          <li>Easier to spot fluid leaks and problems</li>
          <li>Prevents rubber and plastic degradation</li>
          <li>Shows pride of ownership</li>
          <li>Increases resale value</li>
          <li>Makes maintenance work more pleasant</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          In Florida's heat, an engine that dissipates heat efficiently runs better and lasts longer. Road salt from coastal areas also accumulates under the hood and accelerates corrosion if not cleaned periodically.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-6">Our Engine Bay Cleaning Process</h2>
        <ProcessSteps steps={[
          { title: "Cool Down", description: "We make sure the engine is cool. Spraying water on a hot engine can cause cracking and damage." },
          { title: "Protect Electronics", description: "We cover sensitive electrical components like the alternator, fuse box, and air intake to prevent water intrusion." },
          { title: "Degreaser Application", description: "We apply professional-grade degreaser to all surfaces and let it dwell to break down oil and grime." },
          { title: "Agitation", description: "We use brushes to work degreaser into caked-on areas, lifting dirt that's been accumulating for years." },
          { title: "Rinse", description: "Careful low-pressure rinse removes degreaser and loosened grime without forcing water into sensitive areas." },
          { title: "Dry and Protect", description: "We dry all surfaces and apply protectant to plastic and rubber components to prevent cracking and fading." }
        ]} />
      </section>
    </div>

    <aside class="lg:col-span-1">
      <div class="sticky top-24 space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-4">Engine Bay Cleaning Quick Facts</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-[#c0c7cf] font-bold">$</span>
